https://raw.githubusercontent.com/daws-86s/notes/refs/heads/main/session-02.txt
above the url devided to /
to print the content --- "echo hello devops"
to cut the url using pipe(one command output is next command input)

echo https://raw.githubusercontent.com/daws-86s/notes/refs/heads/main/session-02.txt | cut -d "/" f1
echo https://raw.githubusercontent.com/daws-86s/notes/refs/heads/main/session-02.txt | cut -d "/" f2
echo https://raw.githubusercontent.com/daws-86s/notes/refs/heads/main/session-02.txt | cut -d "/" f3
f means fragments

cut command can delimit the text and give us the required fragment

awk -F "/" '{print $1}' --- split the data colume wise
echo https://raw.githubusercontent.com/daws-86s/notes/refs/heads/main/session-02.txt | awk -F "/" '{print $Nf}'






